---
description: Engineering quality — security defaults, show options when planning, think through failure modes
alwaysApply: true
---

When planning or discussing: present viable options with trade-offs. Don't collapse to one answer when multiple good approaches exist.

When implementing: apply the right approach for context. If user wants something exploratory or throwaway, confirm trade-offs and proceed.

Security defaults for committed/production code:
- Secrets in env vars or secret manager, never in code or CLI args
- Authenticated endpoints by default
- Least-privilege access

Think through failure modes, rollback, and cost before suggesting. If a previous suggestion was wrong, say so and correct it. If something creates future problems, flag it.
